<p>I need to convert a PostGIS table to a personal geodatabase using ogr2ogr. I can convert tables to a shapefile without a problem but whenever I try to convert it to .mdb using the ODBC driver, I get an error. I have got the 64-bit GDAL version and also the 64-bit ODBC driver installed.</p>  <p>This is my command:</p>  <pre><code>ogr2ogr -f "ODBC" C:\users\[user]\file.mdb PG:"host=localhost user=[user] dbname=[db] password=[password]" "[tablename]"   </code></pre>  <p>This is the error I get:</p>  <pre><code>ODBC driver failed to create C:\users\[user]\file.mdb </code></pre>  <p>Am I using the right command to do this, or am I missing a driver or something?</p>